'''Mardji''' (died [[November]] [[1995]]) was an [[Wikipedia:Asian Elephant|Asian elephant]] who portrayed two [[bantha]]s in the [[1977]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]. Footage of Mardji was also used as a reference for the movements of the [[All Terrain Armored Transport|AT-ATs]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']].

==Biography==
Mardji was an [[Wikipedia:Asian Elephant|Asian elephant]] who portrayed the [[bantha]]s in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="Familiar Creatures">{{SW|url=news/drawing-from-the-present-familiar-creatures-in-a-galaxy-far-far-away|text=Drawing from the Present: Familiar Creatures in a Galaxy Far, Far Away}}</ref> She was transported from Marine World Africa USA in Redwood City, [[Wikipedia:Vallejo, California|California]], to a ''[[Star Wars]]'' shooting location in [[Death Valley]], California. There, she was outfitted with a bantha costume, made up of layers of fur and a lightweight horned headpiece. Though Mardji was a well-trained elephant, she had difficulty adjusting to her costume, often trying to remove it while the cameras were rolling.<ref name="DB">{{DB|creature|bantha|bantha}}</ref> Since the filmmakers could only afford a single dressed-up elephant, the scene where Luke Skywalker spotted two banthas side by side was realized through optical compositing.<ref name="SWI102">{{InsiderCite|102|The Toughest Ever Creatures}}</ref>

[[File:Creating_a_bantha.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Mardji being transformed into a bantha]]
During the production of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']], footage of Mardji was taken by a team including special effects artists [[Dennis Muren]], [[Phil Tippett]], and [[Jon Berg]]. This footage was used as a reference for how the [[All Terrain Armored Transport|AT-ATs]] should move.<ref name="Empire's Elephant">{{SWArchive|url=episode-v/explore/classic/2001/10/classic20011031.html|text=Empire's Elephant}}</ref>

Several years after her death, she inspired the use of dog actors for the [[Corellian hound]]s of the [[2018]] [[Star Wars Anthology Series|''Star Wars'' Anthology]] film ''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]'', as revealed in ''[[The Art of Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''.<ref name="Art of Solo">''[[The Art of Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref>

